  "title": "Intern / Executive Assistant (6-months contract)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>1. Research Support</strong></h3><p>·       Assist in conducting desk research, literature reviews, and data compilation for ongoing and upcoming research projects.</p><p>·       Support the development of research tools (e.g., surveys, interview guides) and help coordinate fieldwork where needed.</p><p>·       Compile, organise, and maintain research data and documentation for internal reference and reporting.</p><p>·       Assist in preparing research summaries, reports, and presentation materials.</p><h3><strong>2. Engagement & Stakeholder Support</strong></h3><p>·       Support planning and coordination of engagement activities, dialogues, workshops, and focus group discussions.</p><p>·       Assist in liaising with community partners, stakeholders, and participants.</p><p>·       Help prepare event materials, logistics, registration lists, and follow-up documentation.</p><h3><strong>3. RED Space Operations</strong></h3><p>·       Assist in the day-to-day running of RED Space, including booking, programme facilitation, and upkeep of resources.</p><p>·       Support documentation of activities, including maintaining records, attendance, and resource inventories.</p><p>·       Ensure smooth coordination and logistics for programmes run at RED Space.</p><h3><strong>4. Administrative & General Support</strong></h3><p>·       Provide administrative support such as scheduling, minute-taking, preparing documents, and filing.</p><p>·       Support communications tasks (e.g., drafting simple content, assisting with information materials) as required.</p><p>·       Assist with any other ad-hoc duties related to RED’s research and engagement initiatives.</p><p>Only shortlisted candidate will be invited for an interview session.<br /></p>",
